Analysis of Main Target Image  
• Block Count & Layers  
  – There are 4 total blocks in the structure.  
  – They form 2 layers:  
     1st (bottom) layer: 3 blocks (a red arch in the center plus two orange wedges at left/right).  
     2nd (top) layer: 1 green rectangular block.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – Center: A single red arch block sits on the bottom.  
  – Left & Right: One orange wedge on each side of the arch, sloping downward away from the arch.  
  – Top: A short green rectangular block laid horizontally across the top of the arch.  

Selection of Required Blocks from Dictionary  
• Red Arch Block: Index 1 matches the wide front‐to‐back arch as shown.  
• Orange Wedges:  
  – Left side wedge: Index 14 (slopes upward toward the right).  
  – Right side wedge: Index 13 (slopes upward toward the left).  
• Green Rectangular Block (horizontal orientation): Index 6.  

Block Indices Needed: [1, 14, 13, 6]  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 14  
  Step3: Move block with index 13  
  Step4: Move block with index 6  
}
